Sounds like staggered animations. 
Basically you can create an animation controller and set the total duration time.
Then, you can create the separate tweens for each animation you want to perform. For each tween you can define a curve, for that curve you can define an interval in percentage of the total duration of the animation. There is a pretty good example in flutter.dev when you search for staggered animations. Note: they don&#39;t have to be one after another, despite the name, they can be fired at the same time, but end and different time like you want. I&#39;m not sure if it is approriate to give answer with just sharing the link to the flutter docs, but here it is
https://flutter.dev/docs/development/ui/animations/staggered-animations.
I have done something similar, but with 2 controllers, which I fire at the same time, but they have different durations.

